==Personal life==
Lee lives in [[Larchmont, New York|Larchmont]], in [[Westchester County, New York|Westchester County]], [[New York]], with his wife Jane Lin, a [[microbiologist]], whom he married in 1983. They have two sons, Haan (born 1984), and Mason (born 1990).<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.nytimes.com/2007/11/25/nyregion/nyregionspecial2/25Rleenj.html?ref=nyregionspecial2 | work=The New York Times | title=A Chicken Coop, but No Tigers | first=Jennifer | last=Frey | date=November 25, 2007 | accessdate=April 25, 2010}}</ref> Lee is a [[naturalized]] US citizen<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.variety.com/article/VR1117973407/?refcatid=1043|title=Taiwan breaking the arthouse mold|last=Frater|first=Patrick|publisher=''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]''|date=October 4, 2007}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://articles.latimes.com/2009/aug/27/entertainment/et-lee27|title=Ang Lee, hippie?|last=Abramowitz|first=Rachel|publisher=''[[Los Angeles Times]]''|date=Aug. 27, 2009}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://web.archive.org/web/20120221222503/http://www.chinapost.com.tw/news/2007/09/25/123903/Ang-Lee.htm|title=Ang Lee 'very satisfied' new film shown in entirety|publisher=''[[The China Post]]''}}</ref> and a [[Buddhist]].<ref>http://rogerebert.suntimes.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=/20121117/PEOPLE/121119978</ref> His younger son Mason Lee starred in the Hollywood blockbuster movie ''[[The Hangover Part II]]'' as Teddy.

==Filmography==
Lee has been involved in the process of filmmaking in various capacities, though the highlight of his career and legacy is his directorial work. The following are Lee's various credits.
